Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.29,0:00:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“They.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.45,0:00:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“They gathered them together \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.32,0:00:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“to the place that is called in Hebrew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.36,0:00:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Armageddon.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.36,0:00:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are “they”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.30,0:00:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is being “gathered”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.90,0:00:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is the significance of that to us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.24,0:00:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as we go about our sacred service today? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.87,0:00:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The answers can be found in the context. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.31,0:00:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I invite you to find Revelation chapter 16, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.98,0:00:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s begin reading in verse 13, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.92,0:00:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.92,0:00:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“And I saw three \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.99,0:00:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“unclean inspired expressions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.00,0:00:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“that looked like frogs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.47,0:00:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“come out of the mouth of the dragon \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.63,0:00:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“and out of the mouth of the wild beast \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.34,0:00:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“and out of the mouth of the false prophet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.27,0:01:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“They are, in fact, \Nexpressions inspired by demons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.28,0:01:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they perform signs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.75,0:01:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they go out to the kings \Nof the entire inhabited earth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.55,0:01:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to gather them together to the war \Nof the great day of God the Almighty.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.56,0:01:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And verse 16 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.86,0:01:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“And they [these “expressions”] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.93,0:01:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“gathered them \N[“the kings of the entire inhabited earth”] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.80,0:01:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to the place that is called \Nin Hebrew Armageddon.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.37,0:01:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“Expressions.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.54,0:01:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these must be \Nvery persuasive expressions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.54,0:01:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because they compel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.81,0:01:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,not just a few isolated kings here and there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.05,0:01:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but “the kings of the entire inhabited earth” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.58,0:01:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to this situation called Armageddon. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.09,0:01:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these expressions, \Nyou notice, are unclean, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.73,0:01:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so they cannot originate with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.26,0:01:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, they are inspired \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.40,0:01:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—“inspired by demons.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.30,0:02:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, \Nthey have their ultimate source \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.91,0:02:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in “the mouth of the dragon,” \NSatan the Devil \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.34,0:02:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—“the father of the lie.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.34,0:02:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But, now, \Nwho actually gives voice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.58,0:02:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to these expressions? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.75,0:02:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, notice in verse 13 that the expressions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.29,0:02:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,also ‘come out of the mouths \Nof the wild beast and the false prophet’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.29,0:02:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,—political entities of Satan’s world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.96,0:02:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have \Nunclean expressions inspired by demons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—originating with Satan but voiced, repeated, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.80,0:02:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,parroted, and echoed by people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.30,0:02:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,who constitute Satan’s wicked world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.31,0:02:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But, now, just what are these expressions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.78,0:02:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that are so persuasive \Nthat they compel kings? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.65,0:02:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What concept would be so compelling? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.79,0:02:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Since 1914, \NSatan has been stepping up his efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.19,0:02:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to mislead “the entire inhabited earth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of his goals \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.80,0:03:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is to deceive mankind \Ninto thinking that humans\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.47,0:03:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,—that Satan’s way of ruling is the best—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.77,0:03:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that humans can actually achieve \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.24,0:03:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,peace and security \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.51,0:03:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,through their own systems and governments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.95,0:03:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, \Naccording to 1 Thessalonians 5:1-3, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.45,0:03:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they will soon be saying \Nthat they have actually achieved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.09,0:03:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“peace and security.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.09,0:03:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, adding to the power \Nof these inspired expressions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.36,0:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are the signs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.06,0:03:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The signs make it seem \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.57,0:03:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,as if these expressions \Nare actually coming true \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.37,0:03:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps that they \Neven have the backing of God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.81,0:03:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But the only god backing \Nthese particular inspired expressions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.81,0:03:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is “the god of this system of things.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.52,0:03:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it unprecedented \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.69,0:04:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that Satan the Devil would use miracles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.29,0:04:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in an attempt to lend credibility \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.36,0:04:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to his ideas, his wicked lies? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.37,0:04:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At Exodus 7:10-12, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.37,0:04:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah empowers Aaron’s rod \Nto become a snake, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.57,0:04:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but Pharaoh’s magic-practicing priests \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.28,0:04:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,mimicked that very sign. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.48,0:04:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, they mimicked the first \Nand the second of the Ten Plagues. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.42,0:04:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, but what about after the Christian \Ncongregation came into existence? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.19,0:04:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul indicated at 2 Thessalonians 2:3-12 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.73,0:04:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that the apostate movement, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.73,0:04:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,which eventually gave birth \Nto the clergy of Christendom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.90,0:04:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,would be backed \N“by the operation of Satan \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.90,0:04:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“with every powerful work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.07,0:04:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and lying signs and wonders.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.44,0:04:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—2 Thessalonians 2:9. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:04:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, Mark 13:22 says—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.72,0:05:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In the prophecy of the last days, Jesus said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.45,0:05:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“False Christs and false prophets \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.19,0:05:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“will arise and will perform signs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.46,0:05:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“and wonders to lead astray, if possible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.39,0:05:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[even] the chosen ones.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.10,0:05:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, clearly, demons teach. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.73,0:05:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is not beyond Satan and the demons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.77,0:05:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to back up their false claims \Nwith wonders at times, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.54,0:05:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,although, obviously, \Ntheir power in that regard is limited. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.61,0:05:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A subtle reminder of that fact \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.15,0:05:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is found at Revelation 16:16, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.02,0:05:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which says that they are ‘gathered together \Nto the place called Armageddon,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.32,0:05:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“to the war of the great day \Nof God the Almighty.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.86,0:05:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Almighty”\N—only Jehovah can hold that title. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.90,0:05:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that very word \Nis a guarantee that Jehovah’s will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.03,0:05:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,will ultimately prevail.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, is it possible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.14,0:06:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that some professed Christians \Ncould start to believe \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.11,0:06:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“expressions inspired by demons” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.18,0:06:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that “perform signs”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If it weren’t possible, \Nat least for individuals, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.72,0:06:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then why would \NRevelation chapter 16 contain this warning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.13,0:06:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the middle of the discussion \Nabout Armageddon that we just read? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.46,0:06:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The verse that we skipped, verse 15, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.13,0:06:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,contains a very relevant reminder \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.70,0:06:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for each and every one of us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.74,0:06:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sometimes we skip it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.11,0:06:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because we keep all the verses \Nabout Armageddon together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.11,0:06:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But, this is not an afterthought, a sidebar, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.48,0:06:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,just a wise saying \Nplunked in for no apparent reason. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.85,0:06:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s totally relevant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.31,0:06:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read it: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.45,0:06:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look! [verse 15] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.12,0:06:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am coming as a thief. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.65,0:06:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy is the one who stays awake \Nand keeps his outer garments, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.69,0:06:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that he may not walk naked \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.99,0:06:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and people look upon his shamefulness.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:06:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we are, right on the cusp \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of the outbreak of the great tribulation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.17,0:07:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You have an identity\N—“garments”—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.98,0:07:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,an identity \Nas a faithful witness of Jehovah God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.92,0:07:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your identity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.92,0:07:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.72,0:07:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,By keeping awake spiritually.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.45,0:07:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The article from which our text is taken,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,entitled\N“‘Your Deliverance Is Getting Near’!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.69,0:07:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the July 15, 2015, issue \Nof The Watchtower, points out\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.36,0:07:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,—in harmony with the Scriptures, \Nboiling down a number of Scriptural facts—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.33,0:07:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that Babylon the Great will be destroyed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.43,0:07:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the initial part \Nof the great tribulation will be cut short. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.81,0:07:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be a brief respite, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.11,0:07:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,during which the majority of mankind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.11,0:07:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,will seek refuge in human organizations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.68,0:07:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Our message of good news \Nwill change to one of judgment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.68,0:07:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the coalition of nations \Nreferred to as Gog of Magog \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,will be bent on attacking \NJehovah’s anointed ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.43,0:08:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and their associates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.56,0:08:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, only loyal love for Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.63,0:08:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and obedient support \Nof his anointed ones will get us through. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.24,0:08:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That will mean everything!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.34,0:08:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what must we do now? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.24,0:08:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay awake. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.85,0:08:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You have an identity\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.88,0:08:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—not just a Bethelite or Gilead graduate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.25,0:08:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.29,0:08:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve worked hard, with Jehovah’s help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.32,0:08:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to establish an identity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.46,0:08:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as a Christian worshipper of Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.09,0:08:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,—keep it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.63,0:08:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Perform “holy acts of conduct.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.20,0:08:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We could say, \Nthings we don’t do\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.60,0:08:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,—things we don’t watch, \Nthings we don’t read, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,things we don’t think about, \Nthings we don’t say. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.88,0:08:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t let the demons tamper \Nwith your identity as a Christian \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.88,0:08:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with their “unclean inspired expressions.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:08:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Perform “deeds of godly devotion,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.65,0:09:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we could say, \Nthings we do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.52,0:09:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,—preaching, lingering in prayer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,continuing in your personal study. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.53,0:09:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Much is covered in Gilead, \Nyes, but not everything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.10,0:09:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The online Study Bible is amazing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and it just keeps getting \Nbetter day after day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.90,0:09:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,helping us to forge a closer bond, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.04,0:09:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a close personal attachment, \Nwith Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.84,0:09:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue devoting time \Nto such “deeds of godly devotion” now \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.82,0:09:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will succeed then. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.82,0:09:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You will not be duped by the expressions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.89,0:09:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that perform signs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.92,0:09:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as others are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.93,0:09:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you will survive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.93,0:09:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“the great day of God the Almighty,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.43,0:09:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,now so very near at hand.\N
